# Agent / crew map (conceptual — implementation in `backend/app/agents`, flows, services)

Prospecting → Qualification → Proposal → Negotiation → Closing → Post-sale/Support. Each stage may map to supervisors + tool plugins (Salesforce, WhatsApp, Stripe, voice, contracts) within OpenClaw boundaries — **no external RAG SaaS as the system of record**; use native knowledge + CRM grounding.

## Sovereign Program Locks

- **3 Action Classes:** Auto-execute, Execute with mandatory approval, Human-only
- **3 Approval Classes:** L1 (manager), L2 (VP + compliance), L3 (C-suite / board)
- **4 Reversibility Classes:** R1 (fully reversible), R2 (reversible with cost), R3 (partially reversible), R4 (irreversible, pre-approval required)
- **5 Sensitivity Levels:** Public, Internal, Confidential, Restricted, Board-Only
- **Provenance Trio:** Every AI recommendation carries data sources, freshness timestamp, confidence score

## Connector Facade Pattern

Every external connector implements: contract, version, retry policy, timeout, idempotency key, action class, audit mapping, telemetry mapping, compensation notes. See `docs/SOVEREIGN_ARCHITECTURE.md` for full specification.

